But then we missed a weekend away together,

264
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:30,180
and things kind of unraveled...

265
00:12:30,910 --> 00:12:32,420
...because of you.

266
00:12:33,680 --> 00:12:35,000
Happy birthday.

267
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:37,520
Ross, Rachel promised

268
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:39,060
it would be over by now.

269
00:12:39,060 --> 00:12:40,600
We seriously have to go

270
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:41,620
if we want to get to Vermont.

271
00:12:41,670 --> 00:12:42,880
I called them,

272
00:12:42,890 --> 00:12:44,100
the last train leaves in a half-hour.

273
00:12:44,150 --> 00:12:46,050
And I have a massage client soon.

274
00:12:46,100 --> 00:12:48,900
You guys, just, please, a little bit longer.

275
00:12:48,950 --> 00:12:49,810
I promise,

276
00:12:49,810 --> 00:12:51,540
Rachel will be back with the cake any minute.

277
00:12:51,590 --> 00:12:54,760
Monica, remember the frosting, huh?

278
00:12:55,420 --> 00:12:57,050
All right, five more minutes.

279
00:13:00,070 --> 00:13:01,160
Hello?

280
00:13:02,100 --> 00:13:03,540
Oh, no, what happened?

281
00:13:04,220 --> 00:13:06,480
Okay, okay, where are you?

282
00:13:06,940 --> 00:13:08,630
Okay, I'll be right there.

283
00:13:09,370 --> 00:13:10,250
Was that Emma?

284
00:13:10,250 --> 00:13:10,890
Is she up?

285
00:13:12,150 --> 00:13:14,290
Rachel got pulled over for speeding.

286
00:13:14,340 --> 00:13:15,790
She forgot her license.

287
00:13:15,790 --> 00:13:16,700
I have to bring it to her.

288
00:13:16,750 --> 00:13:19,120
If you're leaving, I'm definitely going.

289
00:13:19,170 --> 00:13:22,170
Wait, if anybody gets to go, it's us!

290
00:13:22,220 --> 00:13:24,120
We've been complaining the longest!

291
00:13:25,060 --> 00:13:27,640
No, wait, you guys. No, you can't leave.

292
00:13:27,690 --> 00:13:30,590
Rachel already feels bad that the cake's messed up.

293
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:32,760
How do you think she'll feel

294
00:13:32,760 --> 00:13:33,740
when she comes back and you're gone?

295
00:13:33,790 --> 00:13:36,220
I don't know. You'll tell us on Monday.

296
00:13:37,910 --> 00:13:40,480
Joey, you're in charge, okay?

297
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:41,650
You make sure nobody leaves.

298
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:42,970
Got it!

299
00:13:45,090 --> 00:13:47,060
Hey! Where do you think you're going?

300
00:13:47,110 --> 00:13:48,620
To the bathroom.

301
00:13:48,670 --> 00:13:50,770
Well, the rest of you get comfortable,

302
00:13:50,820 --> 00:13:52,680
because we are gonna be here for a--

303
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:54,970
Wait, there's a window in there.

304
00:13:55,020 --> 00:13:57,650
No! He's not getting away that easy!

305
00:13:59,570 --> 00:14:01,150
What are you doing?

306
00:14:01,150 --> 00:14:02,140
Get the hell out of here!

307
00:14:09,330 --> 00:14:11,460
Well, that one did not have Emma's face on it.

308
00:14:12,340 --> 00:14:14,040
- No, it did not. - No.

309
00:14:15,210 --> 00:14:17,600
Well, we'd better get going. It's late.

310
00:14:17,650 --> 00:14:19,460
Jack can't drive at night anymore.

311
00:14:19,460 --> 00:14:21,260
He has trouble staying in his lane.

312
00:14:21,310 --> 00:14:23,360
Last winter I went up on a church lawn

313
00:14:23,410 --> 00:14:25,400
and drove right through a manger scene.

314
00:14:25,450 --> 00:14:27,550
The papers thought it was a hate crime.

315
00:14:31,830 --> 00:14:34,330
- Anyway, it was lovely seeing you. - Okay.

316
00:14:34,380 --> 00:14:36,790
- Bye. Bye, dear. - Nighty-night.

317
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:38,460
- Nighty-night. - Bye.

318
00:14:39,340 --> 00:14:41,130
How could you just let them leave?

319
00:14:41,130 --> 00:14:41,810
Hey, hey, hey.

320
00:14:41,810 --> 00:14:43,170
I'm not gonna mess with Jack.

321
00:14:43,220 --> 00:14:45,170
He's a great man. He fought for our country.

322
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,130
No, he didn't.

323
00:14:47,130 --> 00:14:48,420
He pretended to be a Quaker

324
00:14:48,420 --> 00:14:49,550
to get out of Korea.

325
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:53,910
Well, that's it. He's the last one to go.

326
00:14:53,910 --> 00:14:55,000
I'm locking you guys in.

327
00:14:56,050 --> 00:14:57,420
You do know I can just turn them

328
00:14:57,420 --> 00:14:58,790
the other way around, right?

329
00:14:59,940 --> 00:15:02,080
Oh, I forgot you used to live here.

330
00:15:07,530 --> 00:15:10,400
- Hello? - Joey, it's Estelle.

331
00:15:10,450 --> 00:15:13,780
- Hey. - So how'd your audition go today?

332
00:15:13,830 --> 00:15:15,200
What audition?

333
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:17,340
The one I told you about last week.

334
00:15:17,390 --> 00:15:19,610
What? You never said anything about an audition.

335
00:15:23,220 --> 00:15:25,220
Let me start over.

336
00:15:25,230 --> 00:15:27,740
I just got a call about an audition.

337
00:15:28,580 --> 00:15:30,490
I think you can still make it.

338
00:15:30,540 --> 00:15:32,660
It's down at the Astor Theater,

339
00:15:32,710 --> 00:15:34,810
and you need to have a monologue prepared.

340
00:15:34,860 --> 00:15:37,000
A monologue? I don't have a--

341
00:15:40,780 --> 00:15:41,990
I got it.

342
00:15:43,870 --> 00:15:46,340
So I'm gonna take off.

343
00:15:46,390 --> 00:15:47,130
What?

344
00:15:47,130 --> 00:15:48,890
No, wait! You don't get to leave.

345
00:15:48,940 --> 00:15:52,160
I've got a massage client waiting outside my door any minute.

346
00:15:52,210 --> 00:15:54,200
And we paid for a room

347
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,360
that we're supposed to be in right now!

348
00:15:55,410 --> 00:15:56,900
Well, okay, now...

349
00:15:57,300 --> 00:15:59,550
...only one of us has to stay with Emma.

350
00:16:00,490 --> 00:16:03,100
Okay, and as the person who realized that, I get to go.

351
00:16:03,620 --> 00:16:05,390
No...

352
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:08,270
Let's figure out a fair way to decide who's staying.

353
00:16:08,550 --> 00:16:10,430
Oh, I got it.

354
00:16:10,750 --> 00:16:13,460
Okay, everyone pick a number from one to 10, all right?

355
00:16:13,510 --> 00:16:16,400
Whoever gets the highest number gets to go first.

356
00:16:18,810 --> 00:16:20,320
Okay, 10.

357
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:21,280
Okay, Monica picks 10. I call nine.

358
00:16:21,330 --> 00:16:22,510
Anyone else?

359
00:16:24,020 --> 00:16:26,870
- No, let's just draw straws. - Okay.

360
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:28,960
Or we could flip a coin and multiply the answer--

361
00:16:29,010 --> 00:16:31,380
- I'm begging you to stop. - Right.

362
00:16:31,970 --> 00:16:33,380
Okay, how about this?

363
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:35,580
We got wind-up toys for Emma.

364
00:16:35,630 --> 00:16:36,730
We can make them race,

365
00:16:36,730 --> 00:16:39,120
and whoever comes in last stays.

366
00:16:39,170 --> 00:16:40,870
Yeah, let's do that!

367
00:16:41,750 --> 00:16:42,860
That sounds more fun than the thing

368
00:16:42,870 --> 00:16:44,460
we were gonna do in Vermont!

369
00:16:44,620 --> 00:16:47,270
Okay, everybody, pick your toys!

370
00:16:47,270 --> 00:16:48,600
Okay. I want the dolphin!

371
00:16:48,650 --> 00:16:50,820
- That's a bear! - I'm too excited!

372
00:16:52,380 --> 00:16:54,030
Phoebe, you get the bear.

373
00:16:54,030 --> 00:16:55,370
Joey, you get the robot.

374
00:16:55,420 --> 00:16:56,390
Oh, yeah.

375
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:57,600
And Chandler and I get the dog.

376
00:16:57,650 --> 00:17:02,160
And the race is going to go from here to here.

377
00:17:02,210 --> 00:17:05,570
Now, the one who comes in last stays!

378
00:17:05,620 --> 00:17:06,950
Okay, ladies and gentlemen,

379
00:17:06,950 --> 00:17:07,830
wind your toys.

380
00:17:08,020 --> 00:17:11,350
Okay. On your mark, get set, go!

381
00:17:11,350 --> 00:17:12,460
Go! Go!

382
00:17:12,510 --> 00:17:14,160
Come on, robot!

383
00:17:16,040 --> 00:17:18,030
What are you barking at?

384
00:17:24,130 --> 00:17:26,300
Well, how is that gonna help?

385
00:17:26,790 --> 00:17:28,080
I bought you!

386
00:17:28,080 --> 00:17:30,440
How did I forget that that's all you do?

387
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:33,250
Way to go, robot!

388
00:17:33,690 --> 00:17:35,340
Good job, Alan.

389
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:37,730
Hey, good race, you guys.

390
00:17:37,730 --> 00:17:38,900
Yeah, see you later.

391
00:17:38,950 --> 00:17:41,120
No. No, no. Wait.

392
00:17:41,170 --> 00:17:42,900
We didn't lose.

393
00:17:43,150 --> 00:17:44,580
The rules clearly stated that

394
00:17:44,630 --> 00:17:47,590
the last one to cross the finish line was the loser.

395
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:48,790
Well, our dog never crossed

396
00:17:48,790 --> 00:17:50,940
the finish line. So technically--

397
00:17:50,990 --> 00:17:52,130
They left.

398
00:17:58,230 --> 00:17:59,880
There isn't time to go to the bakery.

399
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:01,520
We're gonna come home.

400
00:18:02,060 --> 00:18:03,770
Everybody left?

401
00:18:05,210 --> 00:18:06,380
All right. Well, just tell Emma

402
00:18:06,430 --> 00:18:09,270
that we'll be there as soon as we can. Bye.

403
00:18:11,080 --> 00:18:13,210
- Rachel! - Oh, God, sorry!

404
00:18:13,260 --> 00:18:14,740
I can't believe they gave you a ticket.

405
00:18:14,790 --> 00:18:16,210
You're such a good driver.

406
00:18:18,410 --> 00:18:21,280
- Emma's awake. - Yeah?

407
00:18:22,330 --> 00:18:23,800
I can't believe this.

408
00:18:23,850 --> 00:18:25,760
This is her first birthday,

409
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:27,450
she's awake, we're not even there.

410
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:29,170
Everybody left.

411
00:18:29,180 --> 00:18:30,850
We still have this stupid obscene cake.

412
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:32,630
Hey, maybe I can fix that.

413
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:34,790
You know, try to turn it into something else.

414
00:18:34,840 --> 00:18:37,250
Oh, don't even bother.

415
00:18:37,610 --> 00:18:39,770
We've already ruined her first birthday.

416
00:18:40,190 --> 00:18:40,750
And do you know

417
00:18:40,750 --> 00:18:42,710
how important these early experiences are,

418
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:44,210
Ross? Very!

419
00:18:44,470 --> 00:18:47,100
According to the back cover of that book that you gave me.

420
00:18:48,740 --> 00:18:50,910
Rach, she's not gonna remember this.

421
00:18:52,780 --> 00:18:54,110
I guess.

422
00:18:55,170 --> 00:18:57,220
Oh, I just had such an idea

423
00:18:57,230 --> 00:19:00,300
of what this day would be like, you know?

424
00:19:00,970 --> 00:19:02,740
Emma laughing...

425
00:19:03,390 --> 00:19:05,390
...and everybody gathered around her cake,

426
00:19:05,390 --> 00:19:07,390
singing "Happy Birthday."

427
00:19:07,720 --> 00:19:08,790
And then we would all--

428
00:19:08,840 --> 00:19:11,090
Hey, get out of the road,

429
00:19:11,090 --> 00:19:11,840
you stupid student driver!

430
00:19:13,840 --> 00:19:15,380
They have to learn.

431
00:19:18,150 --> 00:19:19,530
- Hey. - What?

432
00:19:19,580 --> 00:19:20,920
This is not bad.

433
00:19:21,850 --> 00:19:23,360
Oh, my God. Look, you made it into a bunny.

434
00:19:23,360 --> 00:19:26,770
How did you do that?

435
00:19:26,820 --> 00:19:30,160
Well, I just made these two things cheeks.

436
00:19:31,930 --> 00:19:35,110
And then I split this to make ears.

437
00:19:36,010 --> 00:19:38,280
Well, I am very impressed.

438
00:19:38,550 --> 00:19:40,590
Some can sing, some can dance.

439
00:19:40,640 --> 00:19:41,730
I, apparently, can turn phallic cakes

440
00:19:41,730 --> 00:19:43,910
into woodland creatures.

441
00:19:46,340 --> 00:19:49,510
Now, another way to organize your stuffed animals

442
00:19:49,510 --> 00:19:50,780
is by size.

443
00:19:50,950 --> 00:19:53,050
I'm sorry, is this a game

444
00:19:53,050 --> 00:19:53,830
for Emma or for Monica?

445
00:19:55,390 --> 00:19:56,450
Game?

446
00:19:57,130 --> 00:20:00,400
Emma, do you even know it's your birthday today?

447
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:01,490
You're 1.

448
00:20:01,740 --> 00:20:04,660
One year old. That's little.

449
00:20:07,460 --> 00:20:09,180
That's my girl.

450
00:20:10,470 --> 00:20:12,470
That's how old you are.

451
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:14,630
Did I teach her that?

452
00:20:14,630 --> 00:20:16,240
Did I just impart wisdom?

453
00:20:18,930 --> 00:20:20,450
I want one.

454
00:20:21,830 --> 00:20:23,000
Me too.

455
00:20:28,660 --> 00:20:29,710
There's no one around.

456
00:20:29,710 --> 00:20:31,050
Why don't we just take this one?

457
00:20:32,560 --> 00:20:34,560
- And head to Canada. - I was kidding.

458
00:20:34,610 --> 00:20:36,360
I wasn't. Let's get going.

459
00:20:38,140 --> 00:20:40,430
Hey, are Ross and Rachel back?

460
00:20:40,430 --> 00:20:41,200
No, not yet.

461
00:20:41,250 --> 00:20:43,540
Oh, good, I didn't miss the party.

462
00:20:43,590 --> 00:20:45,170
What about your massage client?

463
00:20:45,220 --> 00:20:47,090
I just felt so bad missing this.

464
00:20:47,140 --> 00:20:49,300
So I just slipped him a little something, you know.

465
00:20:50,320 --> 00:20:52,280
As long as I'm back in five or six hours,

466
00:20:52,280 --> 00:20:53,270
it'll be all right.

467
00:20:55,550 --> 00:20:56,580
Okay.

468
00:20:57,160 --> 00:20:59,300
If Ross and Rachel ask,

469
00:20:59,310 --> 00:21:00,920
I've been here the whole time. The whole time.

470
00:21:02,280 --> 00:21:04,330
I've been here the whole time.

471
00:21:05,570 --> 00:21:07,210
Joey, we just saw you come in.

472
00:21:07,260 --> 00:21:09,400
You ran past us on the stairs.

473
00:21:10,540 --> 00:21:12,180
I don't care that you left.

474
00:21:12,230 --> 00:21:14,240
I'm just glad that you're here.

475
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:14,860
Thanks, you guys.

476
00:21:14,910 --> 00:21:15,790
Hey, guys, come on.

477
00:21:15,790 --> 00:21:17,690
You gotta see what Emma just did.

478
00:21:17,740 --> 00:21:20,110
- What? - Emma, how old are you?

479
00:21:20,160 --> 00:21:22,070
How old are you today?

480
00:21:25,790 --> 00:21:29,030
Emma, that's right. You're that many.

481
00:21:29,080 --> 00:21:31,920
Oh, my God, our daughter's a genius.

482
00:21:32,910 --> 00:21:34,800
- This means-- - No! No science camp!

483
00:21:34,850 --> 00:21:39,180
Damn it! I'll put a candle on the cake.

484
00:21:39,910 --> 00:21:43,630
Oh, and, Emma, look at your stuffed animals

485
00:21:43,630 --> 00:21:45,490
lined up so neatly.

486
00:21:46,100 --> 00:21:47,170
Thanks.

487
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:50,900
Okay, here we go.

488
00:21:51,670 --> 00:21:55,190
Emma's first birthday cake.

489
00:21:56,800 --> 00:21:58,430
Go ahead, Emma, blow out the candle.

490
00:21:58,970 --> 00:22:01,250
Come on, Emma. You can do it.

491
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:03,250
What's wrong? Are you okay?

492
00:22:03,250 --> 00:22:04,120
Oh, yeah, nothing.

493
00:22:04,830 --> 00:22:06,670
These are happy tears.

494
00:22:07,560 --> 00:22:09,440
This is just what I wanted.

495
00:22:11,580 --> 00:22:13,450
Hey, you made it into a bunny.

496
00:22:14,980 --> 00:22:16,800
What is wrong with me?

497
00:22:16,850 --> 00:22:18,800
It looked more delicious when it was a penis.

498
00:22:25,740 --> 00:22:27,700
- Okay, you ready? - Yeah.

499
00:22:27,700 --> 00:22:30,560
- And record. - Okay.

500
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:32,350
Hi, Emma.

501
00:22:32,530 --> 00:22:35,160
Well, your first birthday is over, and--

502
00:22:35,160 --> 00:22:36,640
Go! Go! Come on!

503
00:22:36,640 --> 00:22:38,460
Go! Go! Come on!

504
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:44,970
Go! Go, Alan! Run, you hairy bastard!

